INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
This SQ will pull in only failed BTCH_STAT_CD values from the RCIT_CLM_BTCH_CNTL table, where the failed status code is one of the daily batch error codes.
Checking for all these status codes is done so that this can be used to fail multiple workflows for balancing.
BTCH_STAT_CD between 90 and 95 are error status codes for Daily Processing.

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
A session has failed in the Balance CIE Load workflow:
To restart: Modify the RCIT_BTCH_CNTL table: Log into GDXPRD and run the following command: update vrap.rcit_clm_btch_cntl set BTCH_STAT_CD = 8, BTCH_STAT_TS = current timestamp where BTCH_STAT_CD in (9,95)
Log into the RCI Manager Rebates Application Go to Process -> Process Control Click on the Process GID Find step that failed, click on Restart, click on Update It can take up to 15 minutes for the workflow to restart.

%a<$PMTargetFileDir/CIE_Balance_Batch_List.out> At least one of the batches loaded to CIE were found to be out of balance.

Please email _GDXITD if you have any questions.
